		   <br /><nobr><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Decent [3.33]</nobr><br /><br /><a href="/cgi-bin/pm.pl?action=addtolist&addname=Ervyn&type=Address" id="fs8"><img src="/shared/plus.gif" border="0" align="middle" height="9" width="9" alt="Add to address book"> Add to address book</a><br /><img src="/shared/transp.gif" width="135" border="0" height="1"></td><td valign="top" class="mform2" width="100%"><p>When I had to choose my specialization, I though to myself, "What spell am I likely to cast in a pinch that will win or lose my/a groupmate's life?"<br><br>Let's cover the most poular:<br><br>Evocation - killing the mob before he kills you/your groupmate- undeniably needed sometimes.<br><br>Alteration - This one is most often referred to as healing- but let's not forget what else uses alteration, perhaps the most important job a druid has at high levels- EVAC.&nbsp;&nbsp;This is probably the spell that will save you and your group more than anything else.<br><br>Conjuration - doesn't really apply unless they you/your group is dying of hunger or thirst (woo!  Summon water!)<br><br><br>Thus (as you may have guessed) I chose alteration.  I prefer to get that last heal off when the cleric is oom or be able to evac when you're really low on mana.<br><br>Anyway, just my two cents.<br><br>Ervyn Peregrinus<br>40th Druid of Tunare<br><br></p><br /><span class="sm">----------------------------</span><br />Reality is for those who can't face Science Fiction</td></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" class="mform2"><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%"><tr><td id="fs8"></td><td align="right" id="fs8" >1 Replies</td></tr></table>
